repetition is the process of re-experiencing or over-and-over again, as in "The sun rises in the east and sets in the west." In computer programming or writing software, repetition can refer to repeating code or instructions multiple times within a single function or block. For example, in the following C program:

```c
int sum = 0;
for (int I = 1; I <= 5; i++) {
    sum += i;
}
printf("%d\n", sum); // Prints "25"
```

We can see that the `sum` variable has been initialized to 0 at the beginning, and then initialized again (and incremented) within each iteration of the loop. In other words, the `i` variable is repeated in the for loop, which sums up all the values in the range from 1 to 5.

